- The integer array parameter `customers` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `customers` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- The integer array parameter `customers` is a 2D array where each sub-array `customers[i]` represents the arrival time and preparation time of the `i-th` customer.
- The arrival times in the sub-arrays of `customers` are sorted in non-decreasing order.
- The integer result is the average waiting time of all customers.
- The average waiting time is calculated by summing up the waiting times of each customer and dividing by the total number of customers.
- The waiting time of a customer is the difference between the time the chef finishes preparing the customer's order and the time the customer arrived.
- The chef prepares food for customers in the order they were given in the input.